  <p>
    Within Codebase tab systems, <strong>each tab label and their respective tab card can be placed next to each other, in pairs</strong>.</p>
  
  <p>
    A tab label's <code>data-tabs=""</code> refers to its respective card's <code>id=""</code>.
  </p>

  <pre><code>&lt;div class="tabs tabs--top"&gt;

  &lt;div class="tabs__label" data-tabs="tabs-example-1"&gt;Tab Label 1&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div id="tabs-example-1" class="tabs__card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="tabs__card-content"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Tab Content 1&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="tabs__label" data-tabs="tabs-example-2"&gt;Tab Label 2&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div id="tabs-example-2" class="tabs__card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="tabs__card-content"&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Tab Content 2&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Other tabs ... --&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>

  <p>
    Simply swap the tabs modifier class to alter the appearance of the tab system:
  </p>

  <pre><code>&lt;div class="tabs tabs--top"&gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="tabs tabs--side"&gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="tabs tabs--accordion"&gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
</code></pre>

